<HEAD>Inquest: Actress Killed Herself After Stock Losses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BROADSTAIRS, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An actress who drowned last month
off the east coast of England killed herself because she was
depressed over the loss of her savings in the October stock market
crash, according to an inquest.
   Coroner Rebecca Cobb on Tuesday recorded a suicide verdict in
the case of Robin Ross, who used the stage name Wendy Ross and had
appeared on several U.S. television shows, including ``Dallas'' and
``Charlie's Angels.''
   Miss Ross' mother, Virginia, testified that her 33-year-old
daughter had come back to Britain and had ``changed completely''
after losing her money. She reportedly lost $185,000.
   ``She meant for the money she lost to be hers to live on,'' said
Mrs. Ross. ``She hated the thought of being a burden to me.''
   She said her daughter, who had been living in Canada at the time
of the October crash, kept telling her mother she felt poor.
   On April 11, Miss Ross drove to a beach near Broadstairs, swam
out to sea ignoring shouts from passersby and drowned.
</TEXT>
