<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Ireland-Pianos     05-18 0103</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Ireland-Pianos,0106</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>French Place 1st And 3rd In Dublin Piano Competition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   French pianist Philippe Cassard won first
prize in the first Dublin International Piano Competition.
   The 25-year-old performer from Paris received 5,000 Irish pounds
($3,100), a grand piano and bookings for several international
concerts.
   Krzysztof Jablonski, 23, from Wroclaw, Poland, won the second
prize of 3,000 pounds ($1,900).
   Another Frenchman, Francois Killian, 26, also from Paris, won
the third prize of 1,500 pounds ($950).
   The competition, which ended Tuesday night, began May 9 and
attracted 197 contestants from 36 countries. It will be held once
every three years.
</TEXT>
