<HEAD>12-Year-Old Boy Killed in Yard</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Recasts throughout to UPDATE with other boys saying they made
up story about drive-by shooting; no pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>COMPTON, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two children who told police a
12-year-old playmate had been fatally shot by an assailant in a
passing automobile Tuesday afternoon apparently made up the story,
police said.
   Instead, police believe the three boys were playing with a
loaded gun, Sgt. R. Allen said Tuesday night.
   ``Apparently one of the kids was playing with a gun and they
fabricated the story,'' he said.
   The victim was identified as Paul Davis. He was shot while
standing in a yard with two friends, police said.
   ``He was struck in the back and died a short time later at the
hospital,'' Cmdr. Terry Ebert said.
   The other two boys, who were unhurt, at first told police that
Paul was killed by a single shot fired from a car.
   Such assaults have become relatively commonplace among the
gang-infested neighborhoods of south-central Los Angeles and nearby
communities.
   Allen said late Tuesday that homicide investigators still were
talking with the families involved, and a decision had not been
reached on whether any charges will be filed.
