<HEAD>Curran Charges Catholic U. Offer is Back-Door Firing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Catholic University professor the Rev. Charles
Curran, charges the university has effectively fired him by
refusing to offer him a position in his specialty ``with no strings
attached.''
   Curran, whose breach of contract lawsuit against the school is
scheduled to go to trial in September in District of Columbia
