<HEAD>Dukakis Trades Jokes, Good Wishes with Lt. Gov. Murphy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gov. Michael S. Dukakis, relying heavily on the
latest in political humor _ astrology jokes _ appeared at a
birthday party for Lt. Gov. Evelyn Murphy, saying that if he wins,
``this state will be blessed with a great new governor.''
   Dukakis asked the crowd Tuesday night, ``Is there anyone in this
room who doubts who Evelyn Murphy really wants to be the next
president?''
   About 300 people attended the fund-raising event for Murphy,
which marked her 48th birthday. Dukakis appeared about an hour
after the party began and spoke for about five minutes.
   ``But who knows what fate has in store for me,'' he said. ``I
asked an astrologer about the future. She said Ed Meese and I both
will be changing our positions soon.''
   Astrology jokes, predicted Dukakis, ``will be in season'' during
his campaign, even though ``you're looking at a guy that doesn't
know a horoscope from a telescope.''
