<HEAD>Tass Reports Bombing Of Its Office In Guatemala</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Guatemala office of the official Tass news
agency was gutted by two bomb blasts, but the Soviet correspondent
assigned there was unhurt, Tass reported today.
   The news agency said the explosions occurred Tuesday night, and
that a car also was destroyed by the blasts.
   ``The Tass bureau had earlier received a threatening letter from
the ultra-right terrorist organization Mano Blanca (White Hand),''
Tass said.
   Correspondent Alexander Trushin and his wife were not injured,
the news agency said, but did not make clear whether they were on
the scene at the time of the explosions.
   Tass gave no other details.
   Violent attacks on Soviets and their facilities were seldom
reported by the state-run media in the past, but the current
``glasnost'' campaign, which encourages openness, has resulted in
quicker acknowledgement of some such incidents.
</TEXT>
