<2ND_LINE>PM-Transit Bus Crash, 2nd Ld-Writethru, a0656,0346</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Killed, 23 Injured In Bus Crash</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with cause of accident, information about
driver and no charges filed.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By M.R. KROPKO</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CLEVELAND (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus driver may have mistakenly pressed the
accelerator rather than the brake in an accident that killed a
teen-age passenger and injured 23 others, police said today.
   ``The passengers told us after the impact the bus accelerated,''
Patrolman Emil Cielec said of the accident late Tuesday night. ``We
feel she might have stepped on the accelerator instead of the
brake.''
   Cielec said the crash occurred when a car tried to turn left in
front of the bus. The bus struck the car, then lurched out of
control, striking a tree, a utility pole and a fence before grazing
a building, he said.
   The bus driver, Audrey Simmons, 27, was hospitalized in fair
condition with a broken leg. Cielec said she has been a bus driver
about seven months.
   The crash is still under investigation and no charges have been
filed, Cielec said.
   A 13-year-old boy on the Regional Transit Authority bus was
killed when a pole from the fence pierced the boy's side, according
to Cielec. He identified the boy as Bernard Murry of Cleveland. The
boy was on the bus with his aunt, who was not injured.
   Five people, including the bus driver, were admitted to area
hospitals, but none were seriously injured. Eighteen others were
released after treatment. Officials were unable to say how many
people were on the bus.
   The driver of the car was in the middle of three lanes on a
one-way street when he tried to turn left, Cielec said.
   ``He was trying to make a left turn and was struck by the bus,''
Cielec said. ``He said he never saw the bus.''
   Cielec said the utility pole struck by the bus fell on the
driver's car, but the driver was not injured. He said it did not
appear alcohol was involved, but an alcohol test was conducted.
</TEXT>
