<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--DraftRiot     05-18 0140</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Draft Riot,0143</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Teens Rampage Over Military Draft in Resettlement Camp</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LUSAKA, Zambia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 2,000 teen-agers rampaged through a
resettlement camp to protest a government decision to draft them
into military service, the defense minister said Wednesday.
   The youths burned down huts at the Kambi Lombilo camp in the
central Zambian city of Ndola on Monday and smashed furniture, said
Gen. Malimba Masheke.
   The teen-agers were forcibly moved from urban areas three weeks
ago under a state-sponsored program to establish resettlement
centers for jobless youth in cities and towns.
   Masheke, who visited the camp Wednesday, told reporters in
Lusaka, the Zambian capital, that the rioters destroyed makeshift
homes they had built themselves when they first arrived.
   Camps were established last month in Lusaka and Ndola to
accommodate 5,000 jobless boys and girls from Zambia's crowded
urban areas.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
