<HEAD>Brawl, Pie Fight Mark City Council Meeting in Brazil</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: SUBS 3rd graf, `Fernandes' political...' to CORRECT that
Blota punched Fernandes.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A City Council meeting turned into a
slapstick brawl with members punching, kicking and throwing pieces
of cream pie at each other.
   It started Tuesday night when councilman Antonio Carlos
Fernandes showed up with a cream pie he said was ``in honor of
Mayor Janio Quadros, for having 107 of his bills approved.''
   Fernandes' political opponent, Geraldo Blota, criticized the
gesture as silly. Fernandes threw a piece of pie at Blota, who
responded by punching Fernandes in the stomach.
   Members of the council quickly took sides, punching and shoving
each other on the assembly floor. The remainder of the pie was
knocked off a desk and splattered over a journalist covering the
session.
   ``Slapstick in the Sao Paulo Assembly,'' read the headline on a
story Wednesday in the O Globo newspaper of Rio de Janeiro.
   Security guards broke up the fighting and removed the remains of
the cake. After the councilors cleaned up and cooled off, they got
back to business.
