<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Liberace Nephew,0185</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Liberace Nephew Committed To State Mental Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The nephew of the late entertainer Liberace
was ordered to a state mental hospital Wednesday for stabbing his
sister during an argument.
   Lester Lee Liberace, 33, was ordered to Patton State Hospital in
San Bernardino County for a maximum term of seven years by Superior
Court Judge Kathryne Ann Stoltz.
   Liberace pleaded guilty in February to assault with a deadly
weapon in exchange for dismissal of an attempted murder charge.
Under terms of the plea bargain, prosecutors recommended
committment to a state mental hospital for seven years, or until he
was no longer considered a threat to society.
   Liberace stabbed his sister, Ina Liberace, 28, in the stomach
with an 8-inch kitchen knife on Nov. 6.
   He had asked her to take him back to the Chatsworth
Rehabilitation Center, which he had left the day before. He became
impatient and assaulted her, prosecutors said.
   Liberace is the son of the late Rudy Liberace, brother of the
flamboyant pianist who died of complications of AIDS last year.
</TEXT>
