<HEAD>Busch's Son: This Reef's For You, Dad</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT PIERCE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Anheuser-Busch Chairman August
A. Busch recevied a late birthday present from his son, who said he
had trouble figuring out what to get the man who has everything.
   So Peter Busch, a local beer distributor, found the perfect gift
_ an artifical reef.
   The younger Busch donated $10,000 to St. Lucie County's
artificial reef program Tuesday and asked that the reef be named
for his father, president of the St. Louis Cardinals baseball team,
who turned 89 in March. Commissioners agreed and Busch said his
father was overjoyed with his present.
   ``It's kind of tough to give something to a man who has
everything after 89 years,'' he said. ``He's thrilled about having
the reef named for him.''
   Busch said he hopes the donation will spur others to contribute
the $50,000 needed to bring the USS Muliphen, a World War II cargo
ship, to Fort Pierce from Newport News, Va. The Muliphen would be
sunk on the artificial reef 15 miles off the Fort Pierce Inlet.
