<2ND_LINE>PM-Steel Imports,0125</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>March Steel Imports Below U.S. Targets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The United States imported 1.8 million net
tons of steel in March, including about 224,000 net tons of
semi-finished steel for domestic steelmakers, according to the
American Institute for Imported Steel Inc.
   The New York-based trade group said the imports represented 17.2
percent of domestic consumption, well below the Reagan
administration's goal of 18.5 percent.
   AIIS President Erwin L. Klein said Tuesday that semi-finished
imports have been in demand by U.S. rolling mills since early 1988,
Klein said. Semi-finished imports reached 12 percent of total steel
import tonnage in March, he said.
   The institute represents 70 leading steel importers that handle
about 70 percent of imported tonnage.
</TEXT>
