<HEAD>Bell Atlantic Renames Five European Companies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bell Atlantic officials have renamed five of
the European computer maintenance companies acquired in February
from BCE Inc. of Montreal.
   The companies will use ``Sorbus,'' the name of Bell Atlantic's
U.S. computer maintenance company, and an indication of the country
in which they operate, said Louis J. Ross, Sorbus chairman and
president of Bell Atlantic Customer Services Inc. on Tuesday.
   The companies are Sorbus (UK) Ltd., formerly Bell Technical
Services Ltd.; Sorbus France, formerly Eurotechnica SA; Sorbus GmbH
in Germany, formerly Dataway Computer GmbH; Sorbus AG in
Switzerland, formerly Dataway Computer AG; and Sorbus GesmbH,
formerly Dataway Computer NmbH in Austria.
   Bell (UK) Communications Ltd. in the United Kingdom and Eurotech
Italia SpA in Italy also were purchased by Bell Atlantic but will
keep their names.
   The Philadelphia-based Bell Atlantic is the parent company for
telephone companies in Delaware, Maryland, New Jersey,
Pennsylvania, Virginia, West Virginia and the District of Columbia.
