<2ND_LINE>BC-Baxter Name Change,0199</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Baxter Travenol to Change Name to Baxter International</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shareholders of Baxter Travenol Laboratories Inc.
have voted to change the company's name to Baxter International
Inc., effective Wednesday.
   The vote at the annual shareholders meeting Tuesday was part of
a continuing campaign to project a more unified image of the
company and its products, Baxter said in a statement.
   ``The proposal to change the name of our company is much more
than cosmetic,'' Vernon R. Loucks Jr., Baxter's chairman and chief
executive, told shareholders. ``It represents the very core of our
strategy.''
   Baxter acquired American Hospital Supply Corp. in 1985, and
Loucks said company officials ``worked aggressively over the past
two years to unite what was Baxter Travenol with what was American
Hospital Supply Corp.''
   ``That job is not yet finished,'' he said. ``But it is on
schedule. And I can report to you today that we are now one company
working effectively for leadership in health care around the
world.''
   Baxter, based in the Chicago suburb of Deerfield, is a leading
international producer of health-care products, systems and
services. It had 1987 revenue of $6.2 billion.
