<HEAD>Dart Group Buys Half Of Small Supermarket Chain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LANDOVER, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dart Group Corp. announced it has acquired
50 percent of the stock of Jumbo Food Stores Inc., which operates
18 discount grocery stores in Maryland and Virginia.
   Dart Group, which has unsuccessfully tried to acquire some of
the largest retailers in the country in the past several years, did
not reveal the cost of the stock.
   Dart Group, headed by Herbert Haft and his son Robert, and Jumbo
are based here. Jumbo operates its stores as Shoppers Food
Warehouses.
   Representatives of both companies were not immediately available
for comment Wednesday.
   Dart Group owns Trak Auto Corp., a chain of discount auto parts
stores; Crown Books Corp., a chain of discount book stores and Dart
Group Financial Corp., a financial business which purchases
bankers' acceptances.
   Dart Group acquisition targets have included May Department
Stores in 1985, Jack Eckerd Corp. in 1985, Safeway Stores in 1986,
Supermarkets General Corp. in 1987, Dayton Hudson Corp. in 1987 and
Stop & Shop Co. this year.
   In April the Hafts said they intended to buy up to $15 million
in F.W. Woolworth Co. stock.
