   Stocks slipped again this morning in slack
trading after a sharp drop in the previous session, which brokers
blamed on investor apathy and fear of inflation.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrial stocks fell 3.32 to
1,983.09 by 11 a.m. EDT. Broader market indices also fell.
