<1ST_LINE>r f BC-CBOEDiscipline     05-18 0174</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-CBOE Discipline,0180</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>CBOE Takes Disciplinary Action Against Four Traders</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Chicago Board Options Exchange has announced
disciplinary actions against four people.
   In the most serious case, Thomas Urreiztieta Kadala, a former
registered representative in the Caracas, Venezuela, office of
Merrill Lynch, Pierce, Fenner & Smith, was censured and suspended
from exchange membership for one year.
   Kadala was accused of making transactions in the accounts of
three Merrill Lynch customers without the required written customer
authorization.
   Kadala, who did not respond to the allegations, also was accused
of failing to disclose to his subsequent employer, Bear Stearns &
Co., that he had been disciplined in connection with his conduct at
Merrill Lynch and that he had previously been known by another name.
   In the other cases announced Tuesday, an exchange member was
suspended for one week for making trades for his own account while
the account was in deficit, and two former exchange members were
suspended until they file required reports on their income,
expenses and other related financial information.
</TEXT>
