<HEAD>Automaker Reports Record Net Earnings For 1987</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TURIN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Italian automaker Fiat on Wednesday
reported its 1987 earnings rose nearly 10 percent on the strength
of higher sales.
   The board of Italy's largest private-sector company released
consolidated results that included the recently-acquired Alfa Romeo
unit and Snia-BPD, the textile and defense group.
   Fiat reported its earnings rose 9.8 percent to a record 2.37
trillion lire, or $1.9 billion in 1987, up from 2.16 trillion lire
a year earlier.
   Revenue rose to 38.43 trillion lire from 29.33 trillion lire in
1986.
   Sales of the auto division accounted for 22.14 trillion lire in
1987, compared with 16.38 trillion lire a year earlier. Fiat's
production reached as high as 2.037 million cars.
