<HEAD>Hewlett-Packard Reports Earnings Up 25 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALO ALTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hewlett-Packard Co. reported Wednesday
its second quarter earnings rose 25 percent as sales jumped by a
similar amount.
   Earnings for the quarter ended April 30 totaled $202 million, or
82 cents a share, compared with $162 million, or 63 cents a share,
in the same period a year earlier.
   Second quarter revenue rose 24 percent to $2.5 billion, compared
with $2.02 billion for the same quarter in fiscal 1987, the company
said.
   The manufacturer of computers and scientific instruments also
reported orders were up 20 percent for the quarter over the same
period last year.
   For the six months ended April 30, Hewlett-Packard reported
earnings increased 37 percent to $381 million, or $1.53 a share,
compared with $278 million, or $1.08 a share, for the first two
quarters in fiscal 1987.
   Revenue for the six months jumped 25 percent to $4.69 billion
from $3.76 billion in the same period in 1987.
