<1ST_LINE>r f AM-CarbideRecapitalization     05-18 0165</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Carbide Recapitalization,0172</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Slashes Dividend, Plans Stock Offering</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DANBURY, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Union Carbide Corp. on Wednesday announced
it was slashing its quarterly dividend by about 33 percent and
planning an offering of about 15 million shares of common stock as
part of a recapitalization plan.
   The Danbury-based chemical giant said it would reduce the
quarterly dividend from 37{ cents to 20 cents, effective with the
Sept. 1 payment.
   ``The combination of high leverage and high dividend payout of
the past few years is inappropriate for our current business
strategies,'' said Union Carbide Chairman Robert Kennedy.
   ``To maintain that combination when financial strength and
flexibility are required in order to capitalize on the best
investment opportunities in years, especially in chemicals and
plastics, would be shortchanging shareholder value,'' he said.
   The company announced the recapitalization plan in November 1986.
   He said the common stock offering and its proceeds, combined
with dividend reduction, will reduce debt and interest costs and
lower the company's debt-to-capital ratio.
</TEXT>
