<1ST_LINE>r f AM-AlleghenyInternational     05-18 0133</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Allegheny International,0139</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Shareholders Meeting On For Friday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Allegheny International Inc. said Wednesday
its annual shareholders meeting will be held this week as
originally scheduled.
   A federal judge in Pittsburgh on Wednesday overturned a
preliminary injunction issued by U.S. Bankruptcy Court that
temporarily prohibited the meeting from being held.
   Wednesday's ruling clears the way for Friday's meeting and
continuation of a proxy fight between dissident shareholders and
the company.
   Allegheny International Chairman Oliver S. Travers urged
shareholders in a letter Wednesday to reject the efforts of
dissidents to gain majority representation on the company's board.
Travers said the dissidents' board nominees have no experience in
the company's business and no definitive plan for the future.
   The Pittsburgh-based Allegheny International, which is
reorganizing under federal bankruptcy laws, manufactures consumer
products.
</TEXT>
